The paper proposes a novel deep learning model for multi-task learning, which is a common problem in various subfields of computer science such as natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed model involves the use of flexible activation functions, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes two functional regularization methods to improve the performance of the model, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.CL, in that order.
